gomodel:SYNGO_392  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099061 replaced by GO:0098839" , "Rationale: Fig 1A STED imaging of DIV21 rat cortical neurons shows apposed localization of PSD95 and ephrinB3 (extracellular antigen) immunostaining inside spine heads.\n\n- Postsynaptic membrane localization is supported by the PPI of the protein with PSD-95 (the marker protein of the postsynaptic density) in P21 synaptoneurosomes (Fig. 1G, J) and direct PPI of the protein with PSD95 in HEK293T lysates expressing both proteins (Fig 2B). This is important because ephrin B3 is known to localize to (certain) presynapses.\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Dissociated cortical neurons were prepared from embryonic day 17-18 (E17-18) rat cerebral cortex as described previously" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3670-7863" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0912-1514" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_392" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
